ENTRY       EC 2.4.2.57                 Enzyme
NAME        AMP phosphorylase;
            AMPpase;
            nucleoside monophosphate phosphorylase;
            deoA (gene name)
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Pentosyltransferases
SYSNAME     AMP:phosphate alpha-D-ribosyl 5'-phosphate-transferase
REACTION    (1) AMP + phosphate = adenine + alpha-D-ribose 1,5-bisphosphate;
            (2) CMP + phosphate = cytosine + alpha-D-ribose 1,5-bisphosphate;
            (3) UMP + phosphate = uracil + alpha-D-ribose 1,5-bisphosphate
SUBSTRATE   AMP [CPD:C00020];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            CMP [CPD:C00055];
            UMP [CPD:C00105]
PRODUCT     adenine [CPD:C00147];
            alpha-D-ribose 1,5-bisphosphate [CPD:C01151];
            cytosine [CPD:C00380];
            uracil [CPD:C00106]
COMMENT     The enzyme from archaea is involved in AMP metabolism and CO2 fixation through type III RubisCO enzymes. The activity with CMP and UMP requires activation by cAMP [2].
HISTORY     EC 2.4.2.57 created 2014
